CLAUDE.md is the single source of truth for working in this repository. Read it in full before acting: @CLAUDE.md

Do not duplicate guidance in this rule — update CLAUDE.md instead and keep this a pointer.

Critical, non-negotiable (full detail in CLAUDE.md):

- The planning docs in `docs/` are binding; never invent stack, fields, routes, screens, or defaults — if genuinely unspecified, STOP and ask.
- Pre-code repo: verify files/commands/folders exist before assuming (read/grep/run first); never claim things exist or fabricate output. `CURRENT_STEP.md` holds the live next step.
- Don't over-engineer: build only what the current sub-step needs — no new deps beyond the TRD list, no speculative abstraction, no features/fields/endpoints beyond the docs.
- Invariants: org-scoped multi-tenancy, JWT in HTTP-only cookies, 401/403/404 RBAC, PM-gated Completed column, signed-URL file access, persist-then-push notifications, no hard deletes, two-layer validation.
- Every sub-step ships to GitHub on a branch → PR (never to `main`); update `CURRENT_STEP.md` last.
- Full build/test: `./build.ps1`
